Lagdera MP Mohamed Hire yesterday dismissed claims that people from his constituency have illegally settled in Isiolo county. He said residents only moved in search of water and pasture when drought ravaged Northeastern. “They came back after the rains began,” Hire said.At the weekend, Isiolo MP Abdi Koropu said Lagdera pastoralists had illegally settled in his constituency. He urged Eastern and Northeastern regional coordinators to have the borders marked clearly to stop conflicts. Clashes have led to loss of lives, livestock and property. In recent months, peace meetings have been organised to promote coexistence.